text:
Just got out of hospital after Pulmonary Embolism II. 
Hostile higher power that's been trying to keep my hands off Numeric QWERTY went off-leash, but to no avail.
... BTC still over USD100k. Full-spectrum Demiurge fail.
100,000 words of semi-processed fictionally embedded Old High Elvish philology and cultural history, too, it's tragic. Impending AIs hovering around it like vultures.

Pulmonary Embolism is the most gentle "Yeah, you could have been switched off, but you haven't been quite yet" thing imaginable. It's almost insulting. "Hey, I thought mortality was supposed to be super-dramatic!"
Five days in the ICU with Pulmonary Embolism tends to do that. Apologies for the crass materialism.
Unless you're unlucky, death, as far as you're personally concerned, is the lightest and even most vaguely comical thing imaginable. ...
... You carry on, if that's an option, for everyone else (even if just to irritate them), but everyone knows that.
